summaries.short: The staff deals with a mysterious homeless woman; Dr. James implements a new exercise program.
summaries.full: Dr. James decides to implement a geriatric exercise program in the ward, upsetting Patsy. DiDi discloses Patsy's relationship with Dawn to her union rep as proof her homophobic comment wasn't serious. A homeless woman, and her accompanying stench, is suspiciously dumped in the ward. Dawn wins the grand prize in Dr. James' charity raffle. Dr. James considers relocating.

summaries.short: A placid night shift is turned upside down by a new patient and some familiar drunken visitors.
summaries.full: DiDi's nightshift in the ward is turned upside down after the arrival of a new patient and several unwelcome, inebriated visitors. Stopping by after a (lamentable) dinner party, Dr. James attends to her drunken husband Richard's ingrown toenail; a woozy Dawn looks for stopgap comforts in the lounge; and an elderly Swedish tourist shows off her gymnastic chops.

summaries.short: Patsy files a grievance against DiDi; a gentleman caller sends shock waves through the ward.
summaries.full: DiDi ends up in conflict resolution after Patsy files a grievance against her for inappropriate remarks. Dawn learns that intimacy with a co-worker is no guarantee of evaluation immunity. Dr. James and Patsy go head-to-head when she decides to skip the 'Make Someone Happy' orientation. A gentleman caller sends shock waves through the ward.

summaries.short: (Season One Finale) Dr. James' plans change; Patsy goes the distance with Dawn; DiDi recovers a debt.
summaries.full: (Season One Finale) Phyllis (Molly Shannon), the daughter of an ailing patient, gets the travel runaround as her mother's condition worsens, improves, and worsens again. After criticizing a proposal to add men to the ward, Jenna tries to leverage her Cleveland opportunity into concessions from Dr. Stickley. Patsy goes the distance with Dawn; DiDi recovers a debt.

summaries.short: A new supervising nurse, Patsy, arrives at Billy Barnes just in time to have his preconceptions shattered.
summaries.full: In the wake of Beverly's departure, a new (male) Supervising Nurse, Patsy De La Serda, joins the Billy Barnes staff with a customer-centric agenda he's convinced will improve ward efficiency. Patsy soon learns that managing patients--especially a highly uncooperative, un-medicated one named Varla--isn't necessarily improved through customer-service metrics.

summaries.short: Season Two Premiere. Dr. James fights for her research; DiDi asks for a raise; Dawn searches for answers.
summaries.full: Season Two Premiere. Dr. Jenna James' plethora of research projects threatens to take over the ward. A frustrated DiDi asks for a raise; Patsy's 'Lean Green' initiative causes problems; Dawn gets a surprising answer to what's been ailing her. Later, Jenna gets some unwelcome news that leads her to make an unholy alliance.

summaries.short: Dr. Jenna James (Laurie Metcalf) gets reassigned to the extended-care unit of a CA hospital after a public meltdown.
summaries.full: (Series Premiere) It's July 4th at the Billy Barnes Extended Care unit of Mt. Palms Hospital in Long Beach, CA. On her first day of work, Nurse DiDi Ortley discovers feces on a lounge chair, and is torn between the conflicting orders of her co-workers. Meanwhile, the staff tries to determine the identity of a woman found wandering on a highway.
